20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2236A of Title 74, unless there
23 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 12311 Page 1

1 A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma Tourism Ignition
2 Program until November 1, 2027. The Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation
3 Department shall market the program. The Oklahoma Arts Council
4 shall administer the program and promulgate administrative rules
5 necessary to implement the provisions of this section.
6 B. The Council shall accept applications from municipalities
7 within this state to match funds derived from the Department in an
8 amount equal to those funds provided by the municipality, up to Five
9 Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), for allowable expenditures. The
10 Council shall be authorized to approve or deny an application.
11 C. Each municipality shall prepare and submit appropriate
12 plans, including a budget work program, in its application.
13 Expenditures for obligations incurred before the Council approves an
14 application and any changes thereto, and expenditures not in
15 accordance with the municipality's plans and budget work program,
16 shall not be allowable expenditures.
17 D. Allowable expenditures shall be based upon actual
18 expenditures by the municipality less any discount, refund or rebate
19 to the municipality.
20 E. As used in this section, "allowable expenditures" means
21 expenditures by a municipality, submitted to the Council for
22 matching funds, to create a positive economic impact via tourism
23 including, but not limited to, a statue, structure or mural, which
24 would result in tourism revenue in a municipal area.
